    <div class="section">
      <h3>LOCAL EXAMINATION</h3>
      <p><br>
      </p>
      <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<b>&nbsp;&nbsp;
          POSITIONS :</b></p>
      <b> </b>
      <ol>
        <b> </b>
        <li><b>INSPECTION</b></li>
        <b> </b>
        <li><b>PALPATION</b></li>
        <b> </b>
        <li><b>REGIONAL LYMPH NODES</b></li>
        <b> </b>
        <li><b>PURCUSSION</b></li>
        <b> </b>
        <li><b>AUSCULTATION</b></li>
      </ol>
      <p><br>
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; INSPECTION</b></li>
        <ol>
          <p><strong>1. NUMBER:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>SINGLE</li>
            <li>MULTIPLE [NF2, diaphyseal aclasis, nodes]</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>2. SITE:</strong> [midline-dermoid, Line of fusion]</p>
          <ul>
            <li>e.g: outer canthus &ndash; b/w frontonasal, maxillary processes</li>
            <li>post auricular &ndash; b/w mesodermal hillocks of pinna</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>3. EXTENT:</strong></p>
          <p><strong>4. COLOUR:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Black &ndash; naevus, melanoma</li>
            <li>Red &ndash; arterial hemangioma</li>
            <li>Purple &ndash; venous hemangioma</li>
            <li>Bluish &ndash; ranula [mucocele]</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>5. SIZE:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Spheroidal &ndash; of 5cm</li>
            <li>Other shapes &ndash; 4x5cm</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>6. SHAPE:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Irregular</li>
            <li>Spheroidal</li>
            <li>Ovoid</li>
            <li>Pear shaped</li>
            <li>Kidney shaped</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>7. SURFACE:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Smooth</li>
            <li>Irregular &ndash; cauliflower SCC</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>8. SKIN OVER THE SWELLING:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Red, edematous &ndash; I</li>
            <li>Tense, glossy, venous prominence &ndash; N [sarcoma]</li>
            <li>Black punctum &ndash; sebaceous cyst</li>
            <li>Pigmented:
              <ul>
                <li>moles</li>
                <li>naevi</li>
                <li>repeated deep x-rays</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>SCAR
              <ul>
                <li>regular &ndash; injury</li>
                <li>linear scar + suture marks &ndash; surgery</li>
                <li>puckered &ndash; suppurated</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Peau d'orange &ndash; blocked cutaneous lymphatics</li>
            <li>Ulcer &ndash; ULCER CASE SHEET</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>9. SURROUNDINGS:</strong></p>
          <p><strong>10. EDGE:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Clearly defined</li>
            <li>Indistinct</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>11. PEDUNCULATED / SESSILE:</strong></p>
          <p><strong>12. PULSATION:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Toxic STN</li>
            <li>2&deg; of follicular Ca. thyroid [&#8757; functional]</li>
            <li>Aneurysm</li>
            <li>Vascular growths[carotid body tumor]</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>11. PEDUNCULATED / SESSILE:</strong></p>
          <p><strong>12. PULSATION:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Toxic STN</li>
            <li>2&deg; of follicular Ca. thyroid [&#8757; functional]</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>13. VISIBLE PERISTALSIS:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Hernia</li>
            <li>Congenital hypertrophic pyloric stenosis</li>
            <li>Intestinal obstruction</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>14. MOVEMENT WITH RESPIRATION:</strong> Upper abdominal
            viscera</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Liver</li>
            <li>Gall bladder</li>
            <li>Stomach</li>
            <li>Spleen</li>
            <li>Hepatic flexure</li>
            <li>Splenic flexure</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>15. COUGH IMPULSE / Swellings in continuation with IMPULSE
              ON CRYING:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Abdominal cavity</li>
            <li>Pleural cavity</li>
            <li>Spinal canal</li>
            <li>Cranial cavity</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>16. MOVEMENT WITH DEGLUTATION:</strong> Swellings attached
            to larynx/trachea</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Thyroid swellings</li>
            <li>Thyroglossal cyst</li>
            <li>Subhyoid bursitis</li>
            <li>Pre/para tracheal lymphadenitis</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>17. MOVEMENT WITH PROTRUSION OF TONGUE:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Thyroglossal cyst</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>18. PRESSURE EFFECTS LIMB DISTAL TO SWELLING:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Edema of limb - Axillary swelling [lymph node]</li>
            <li>Disuse Atrophy [wasting] - trauma, fracture, plaster cast,
              polio, nerve injury</li>
            <li>Face &amp; neck venous engorgement - retrosternal prolongation</li>
          </ul>
        </ol>
        <p><br>
        </p>
        <li>
          <h2>Palpation: </h2>
        </li>
        <ol>
          <li>GENTLE 3D (May spread malignant)</li>
          <li>LOCAL RISE OF TEMPERATURE
            <ul>
              <li>&acirc;&dagger;&lsquo;ed vascularity - Dorsum of fingers</li>
              <li>Vascularised tumor[sarcoma]</li>
              <li>False +ve &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; subsequent examination</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>TENDERNESS
            <ul>
              <li>Tender &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; I,T see wincing</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>SIZE</li>
          <li>SHAPE</li>
          <li>EXTENT
            <ul>
              <li>Getting above the swelling</li>
              <li>Getting below the swelling</li>
              <li>Extent in all directions</li>
              <li>Lateral border isn't palpable</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>SURFACE
            <ul>
              <li>Smooth &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; cyst</li>
              <li>Lobular with smooth bumps &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; lipoma</li>
              <li>Nodular &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; matted lymph nodes</li>
              <li>Irregular rough &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; Ca.</li>
              <li>Medial part &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; nodular + lateral part -
                smooth</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>EDGE
            <ul>
              <li>Smooth &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; benign (finger tips)</li>
              <li>Irregular &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; malignant</li>
              <li>Well defined &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; I chr. Usually slip N
                benign[lipoma]</li>
              <li>Cyst DD b/w cyst,lipoma
                <ul>
                  <li>Yields, slip sign</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>Indistinct &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; acute I</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>CONSISTENCY (OBO what it's made of)
            <ul>
              <li>Very soft - lipoma</li>
              <li>Cystic &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; cyst, Chr. abscess</li>
              <li>Firm &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; fibroma</li>
              <li>Hard
                <ul>
                  <li>Yielding &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; chondroma</li>
                  <li>Bony hard &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; osteoma</li>
                  <li>Stony hard &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; Ca.</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>Variable &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; malignant (Ca. sarcoma)</li>
              <li>Crepitus
                <ul>
                  <li>Gas gangrene</li>
                  <li>Surgical emphysema</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>Putty like indented
                <ul>
                  <li>Sebaceous cyst</li>
                  <li>Dermoid</li>
                  <li>Faeces in abdominal swelling</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>Pitting edema &acirc;&euro;&ldquo; I</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>FLUCTUATION (if cystic consistency)
            <ul>
              <li>Contains liquid or gas</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>FLUID THRILL</li>
          <li>TRANSLUCENCY</li>
          <li>MOBILITY</li>
          <li>COUGH IMPULSE</li>
          <li>COMPRESSIBILITY</li>
          <li>REDUCIBILITY</li>
          <li>PULSATILITY</li>
